{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f258cdca-6424-47fe-9b03-64bf504c07dc","content":"No repo to inspect — this is a knowledge question. Here's the answer:\n\n## What happened\n\nIn **.NET 11**, `DSA.Create()` throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS**. This is the culmination of a multi-release deprecation:\n\n1. **Apple removed DSA** from its native crypto frameworks (Security.framework / CommonCrypto) years ago.\n2. **.NET 7–10** kept DSA alive on macOS via a **managed/OpenSSL shim**, but marked DSA-related APIs with **`[Obsolete(\"SYSLIB0045\")]`**.\n3. **.NET 11** completed the removal on macOS — `DSA.Create()` now throws at runtime on that platform.\n\nLinux and Windows still have OS-level DSA support, so they continue to work (though the obsolete warnings remain).\n\n## How to fix it\n\n**Option A — Use [BouncyCastle](https://www.nuget.org/packages/BouncyCastle.Cryptography) for legacy verification (recommended)**\n\nThis is cross-platform and doesn't depend on OS crypto primitives:\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\nbool VerifyDsaSignature(byte[] publicKeyBytes, byte[] data, byte[] signature)\n{\n    var keyParam = (DsaPublicKeyParameters)PublicKeyFactory.CreateKey(publicKeyBytes);\n    var verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA-1withDSA\"); // or SHA-256withDSA\n    verifier.Init(forSigning: false, keyParam);\n    verifier.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);\n    return verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n}\n```\n\n**Option B — Conditional runtime fallback**\n\nKeep `System.Security.Cryptography` on Windows/Linux, fall back to BouncyCastle on macOS:\n\n```csharp\nif (OperatingSystem.IsMacOS())\n    return VerifyWithBouncyCastle(pubKey, data, sig);\nelse\n    return VerifyWithSystemDsa(pubKey, data, sig);\n```\n\n**Option C — Migrate away from DSA entirely**\n\nIf you control both signing and verification, re-sign with **ECDSA** or **Ed25519** — both are modern, cross-platform, and fully supported. This is the best long-term path, though it requires re-issuing signatures.\n\n### TL;DR\n\nApple killed DSA → .NET carried it on life-support → .NET 11 pulled the plug on macOS. Use **BouncyCastle** for continued cross-platform legacy DSA verification, or migrate to ECDSA/Ed25519.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a9d640c3-dd6a-445e-a705-a2e04e6a94f2","outputTokens":674,"requestId":"C431:28D4C6:1D13EC1:20E9551:6A07C93A"},"id":"3bb88e05-5493-400d-8f9c-1f543a7f8ba1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:32:56.281Z","parentId":"9ee472f9-d945-4e83-bd49-be94e3ef2e8e"}
